ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if delivered SWC contains all mandatory subfolders

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Check 02_libs content (Libraries delivered)
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks the existance of the libraries in 02_libs folder. At least one library should exist in this folder. Existance should be checked by expected file extension

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Check for mandatory MAP file
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if mandatory MAP file exists in 05_data subfolder. There must be exactly one MAP file

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Check for mandatory MISRA file
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if mandatory MISRA file exists in 05_data subfolder. There must be exactly one MISRA file

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Check for mandatory BUILD LOG files
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if one or more build log files are delivered in 05_data subfolder

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Check for mandatory test cases in the delivery
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if all mandatory test cases are delivered in 04_test subfolder

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Test Case naming convention check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if all delivered Test cases (mandatory and additional) follows the naming convention

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Mandatory Test Case folder content check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if every mandatory test case folder contains all mandatory files.

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Additional Test Case folder content check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if additional test case folder (if any) contains all mandatory files.

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Heap allowed but not used
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if SWC is allowed to use Heap but heap is never been used.

ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Heap used but not allowed
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if SWC using the heap but it is not allowed to use.

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Host check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Check if SWC's host stated in Release Notes document is correct (the same as the one stated in Architecture Model)

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: ASIL level check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Check if SWC's ASIL level stated in Release Notes documents is correct (the same as the one stated in Architecture Model)

ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks the result of the mandatory test cases stated in supplier's AITR document

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Additional test case result check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks the result of the additional test cases stated in supplier's AITR document (if any)

ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Interface check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks symbols used by delivered libraries against the allowed symbol set - white list (RTE symbols from Contract header and specific list of symbols from the Architecture Model)
